
HISTORY !!

> WHAT IS GIT HISTORY -
-- Git helps to keep a detailed record of every change made to our project. 
   We can use history commands to see what changed, when and who made the changes. 
   This will help to track progress , finding bugss and understanding our project's evolution. 

> COMMANDS - 
-- To show full commit history 
   [git log] 
-- To show commit history in one line
   [git log --oneline] 
-- To show detail of a particular commit 
   [ git show <commit> ]
-- To see unstaged changes
   [ git diff ]
-- To see sraged changes 
  [ git diff --staged] 
-- To compare two commits 
  [ git diff <commit1> <commit2> ]
-- To show commits by a specific Author 
  [ git log --author="lolo" ]
-- To show recent commits 
  [ git log --since="1 week ago" ] -> There should not be any gap in between. 

